<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" style="color: #7B2D8E;">Before Your Appointment</h3>

<div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-8">
  <p class="mb-4">
    Before your appointment, it's important to prepare your skin to ensure the best results. You should let the hair grow to at least a quarter inch to allow for the wax to grip it properly. Avoid shaving or trimming the hair before your appointment, as it can make the hair too short to wax. You should also avoid using any lotions, oils, or perfumes on the area being waxed, as they can interfere with the wax adhering to the hair.
  </p>
  <p class="mb-4">
    Avoid taking too much alcohol or caffeine before waxing, as it tightens the pores and makes the process more painful. If you are menstruating, consider rescheduling your appointment. The skin around your pubic bone gets more sensitive, and you will be more prone to cramping and extra discomfort.
  </p>
</div>

<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" style="color: #7B2D8E;">During Your Appointment</h3>

<div class="bg-purple-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-8">
  <p class="mb-4">
    During the appointment, we will clean the area to be waxed and apply warm wax to the hair and quickly remove it, pulling the hair out by the roots. Though it's a simple process, remaining as relaxed as possible is vital. This makes the process easier and less painful.
  </p>
  <p>
    While the waxing process may be uncomfortable, it should not be overly painful. If you experience any pain or discomfort, let your esthetician know so they can adjust their technique.
  </p>
</div>

<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" style="color: #7B2D8E;">After Your Appointment</h3>

<div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-8">
  <p class="mb-4">
